originalText.text:
Lately, the food here is awful. I used to order from them often, but started going to China Wok for better quantity of food and better prices. China Wok is temporarily closed, so I returned to 88. I had vegetable lo mein, and it was overcooked and noodles mushy. Lack of flavor.
Next I tried roast pork with Chinese vegetables--the pork was cut in large pieces and was dried out. No real sauce in the dish, and no flavor.

Finally, I tried fried chicken wings--overcooked (or re-cooked) and that night I got sick. No more. Will wait for China Wok to reopen.

originalText.text: Overall very reliable and tasty food. Though they can be a bit cheap with the meat. Ordered a scallop and garlic dish and it was mostly (80 percent) vegetables with only 6 or 7 pieces of scallops. Though it was very tasty. Place is very clean and service is quick and friendly.
